# Code owners for defect-scan.
#
# Why: in a public repo, CI can prove a proposed check is *noisy* (the eval grader
# fails), but it cannot prove a PR isn't *weakening the grader itself* — deleting a
# clean fixture, editing a .expected to bless a false positive, relaxing a safety
# rule, or altering the deterministic plumbing. Those paths require maintainer review.
# Pair this with branch protection ("require review from Code Owners") to enforce it.

# Default: anything not matched below.
*                                   @stylusnexus/stylus-nexus

# The deterministic engine (incl. the model-free eval grader + issue-filing safety).
/skills/scan/lib/                   @stylusnexus/stylus-nexus

# The eval grader's ground truth — must not be silently weakened.
/tests/eval/                        @stylusnexus/stylus-nexus

# Defect knowledge the model reads (the self-improvement write path).
/skills/scan/profiles/              @stylusnexus/stylus-nexus
/skills/scan/patterns/              @stylusnexus/stylus-nexus
/skills/scan/SKILL.md               @stylusnexus/stylus-nexus

# Security / CI / release machinery.
/SECURITY.md                        @stylusnexus/stylus-nexus
/.github/                           @stylusnexus/stylus-nexus
/release-please-config.json         @stylusnexus/stylus-nexus
